    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A composite material consisting of a body of sintered quartz coupled with an alkaline glaze surface, and used for decorating beads, amulets, figurines, and other small objects. It was invented in Mesopotamia or Iran ca. 4500 BCE, and produced through the mid-7th century CE. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046892/Grove Art Online (2003-2008)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046985/Moorey, Materials and Manufacture in Ancient Mesopotamia(1985)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Samengesteld materiaal bestaande uit een romp van gesinterde kwarts met een oppervlak van alkalisch glazuur, gebruikt voor het decoreren van kralen, amuletten, beeldjes en andere kleine voorwerpen. De techniek is circa 4500 v. Chr. uitgevonden in Mesopotamië, en werd tot halverwege de 7de eeuw n. Chr. toegepast.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種合成材料，由燒結過的石英構成，表面則為鹼性釉料。用於裝飾珠子、護身符、雕像及其他小型物件。約西元前4500年時發明於美索不達米亞或伊朗，一直生產至西元七世紀中。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
